# Environment Variables - Production
# Set these in your deployment platform's environment / secret manager
# (Render: Dashboard → Service → Environment; Vercel: Project Settings → Environment)
# NEVER store production secrets in files!

# ⚠️ CRITICAL: This file is for documentation only
# Set all variables via your platform dashboard or CLI.

# Required Variables:
DATABASE_URL=<managed-postgres-url>
REDIS_URL=<managed-redis-url>
JWT_SECRET=<min-32-char-random-string>
PAYSTACK_SECRET=sk_live_<your-live-key>
PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_live_<your-live-key>
BREVO_API_KEY=xkeysib-<your-api-key>
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<aws-key>
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<aws-secret>
AWS_S3_BUCKET_NAME=suoops-production
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=<twilio-sid>
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=<twilio-token>
FRONTEND_URL=https://suoops.com
ENVIRONMENT=production
SENTRY_DSN=<sentry-dsn>

# How to set on Render:
#   Render Dashboard → suoops-backend → Environment → Add Environment Variable
# Or via Render CLI (https://render.com/docs/cli):
#   render env set JWT_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32) --service suoops-backend

# Verify settings: list env vars in the Render Dashboard or via `render env ls`.
